# Python Proxy Conventions

- All functions that touch MCP messages must be async
- Use dataclasses for Threat and CrossfireEvent, not plain dicts
- Detectors must return list[Threat], never raise exceptions
- Log to stderr only -- stdout is reserved for MCP stdio transport
- Never use print() -- use sys.stderr.write() or logging to stderr
- Import typing at top: Literal, Optional, etc.
- Use asyncio.create_subprocess_exec for spawning servers
- Broadcast failures must be silently swallowed (try/except pass)
- JSON serialization: use separators=(',', ':') for compact wire format
